OL,3,CWarning after walkers cause stampede
OL,4,Cof 250 stressed seals
OL,6,FSue Sayer MBE, from the Seal Research
OL,7,FTrust, said: "Once you've disturbed
OL,8,Fthe seals, you lose that privileged
OL,9,Fview of seeing amazing wildlife in
OL,10,Ftheir natural habitat doing natural
OL,11,Fthings. And not only do you lose that
OL,12,Fsight, but so does everybody else for
OL,13,Fthe rest of the day."
OL,15,FWe are now entering the pupping season
OL,16,Fwhen seals feed their pups on the
OL,17,Fbeaches for three weeks. This ensures
OL,18,Fthe youngest and most vulnerable seals
OL,19,Fwill be fat enough to survive the
OL,20,Fwinter, and not being fed enough due
OL,21,Fto disturbance can be dangerous.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
